    // This means f("011") is 3, not f("11").
    // So, for s_l...s_r, we calculate its value directly.
    // The maximum length is N = 2e5.
    // The maximum value of a binary string of length L is 2^L - 1.
    // If L is large, 2^L - 1 will be much larger than L.
    // For example, if L=18, 2^18 = 262144.
    // If L=19, 2^19 = 524288.
    // If L=20, 2^20 = 1048576.
    // If L=21, 2^21 = 2097152.
    // If L=22, 2^22 = 4194304.
    // If L=23, 2^23 = 8388608.
    // If L=24, 2^24 = 16777216.
    // If L=25, 2^25 = 33554432.
    // If L=26, 2^26 = 67108864.
