        // to minimize |a_i - a_j|, we want i and j to be as close as possible.
        //
        // The crucial observation is that if we split the sorted array into two halves,
        // a_0, ..., a_{n-1} and a_n, ..., a_{2n-1},
        // and assign the first half to Class 1 and the second half to Class 2,
        // then Class 1 has n students and Class 2 has n students.
        //
        // If n is odd, then both classes have an odd number of students.
        // The median of Class 1 (a_0, ..., a_{n-1}) would be a_{(n-1)/2}.
        // The median of Class 2 (a_n, ..., a_{2n-1}) would be a_{n + (n-1)/2} = a_{(3n-1)/2}.
