        // $2k_1+1 + 2k_2+1 = 2n \implies 2k_1+2k_2+2 = 2n \implies k_1+k_2+1 = n$.
        //
        // The smallest possible median for any class is $a_0$.
        // The largest possible median for any class is $a_{2n-1}$.
        //
        // The key insight for this type of problem is often that the medians will be "central" elements.
        // If we want to minimize the difference between two medians, we should pick them as close as possible in the sorted array.
        //
        // Consider the elements $a_{n-1}$ and $a_n$.
        // Can $a_{n-1}$ be the median of one class and $a_n$ be the median of another?
        //
