        // The difference is $a_{2n-1} - a_{n-1}$.
        //
        // The minimum value of $a_{n+k_1} - a_{k_1}$ for $0 \le k_1 \le n-1$ is $a_n - a_{n-1}$ when $k_1 = n-1$.
        // No, this is not correct. $a_{n+k_1} - a_{k_1}$ is minimized when $k_1$ is such that $a_{n+k_1}$ and $a_{k_1}$ are close.
        // This is generally when $k_1$ is small.
        //
        // The minimum value of $a_{n+k_1} - a_{k_1}$ is $a_n - a_{n-1}$ if $k_1=0$ and $a_n$ is the median of $C_2$ and $a_0$ is the median of $C_1$.
        //
        // The argument is simpler:
        // Let $M_1$ and $M_2$ be the medians. $M_1 \le M_2$.
        // $M_1$ must be at least $a_{k_1}$ (the $k_1$-th element in the sorted array, 0-indexed).
        // $M_2$ must be at most $a_{2n-1-k_2}$ (the $(2n-1-k_2)$-th element in the sorted array).
        //
