        // If $n$ is even, this partition is not valid because class sizes are even.
        //
        // The problem is simpler: the minimum difference is always $a_n - a_{n-1}$.
        // This is because we can always construct two classes, one with $a_{n-1}$ as median and one with $a_n$ as median.
        //
        // Let $C_1$ be $\{a_{n-1}\}$ and $C_2$ be $\{a_0, \dots, a_{n-2}, a_n, \dots, a_{2n-1}\}$.
