                // N becomes N-1 (odd). Opponent's turn.
                // Opponent will take 1 coin, N-2 (even). Chanek's turn.
                // This path is generally worse for Chanek if N/2 is a good move.

                // Option 2: Take N/2 coins
                // N becomes N/2. Opponent's turn.
                // This is usually the optimal move for Chanek if N is even.
                // The only exception is if N/2 is 2 and N is 4.
